From c1a9409e7fa2e8e4bce12c0062c6999ad9cc53db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 02:19:20 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] hostapd-extn: Add code to integrate extension code with hostapd

240MHz is a QCN feature to support higher bandwidth in a 5GHz band.
This patch integrates the below support:

1. Add a new supporting “op_class = 129” for 240MHz channel width
2. Add support to get the channel numbers for 320Mhz channel width and
total number of these 320MHz width channels (= 16).
3. Support for Number of 240MHz channels.
4. support to parse 240MHz IE from the STA Association Request
5. Add these parsed 240MHz params to global STA params.
6. Support to add QCN IE for 240MHz capability advertisement in the Beacon,
Probe Response, Assoc Response.
7. Correct the channel center frequencies for 240MHz.
8. Sent the STA 240MHz information from hostapd to driver.
9. Currently 240MHz information of the STA is sent to driver through
standard NL attribute - NL80211_ATTR_EHT_240MHZ_CAPABILITY. This is
replaced by the Vendor NL command: QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_240MHZ_INFO

Signed-off-by: Sri Vidya Gunturi <sgunturi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Venkateswara Swamy Bandaru <vbandaru@qti.qualcomm.com>

